column1: table 19.  Supplemental data for 68 large county governments
series title:  Justice Expenditure and Employment Extracts 1998, NCJ 190641
data source:  Criminal Justice Expenditure and Employment Extracts Program (CJEE)
Table 19. Supplemental data for 68 large county governments
Note: Jurisdictions without data did not report for 1998.
a/ Population data are from the Bureau of the Census, July 1, 1998 county population estimates.
b/ "Total general expenditure" excludes utilities, county-operated liquor stores, and insurance trust benefits.
c/ "General functions only" FTE excludes utilities and county-operated liquor stores.
d/ In 1997 Middlesex County in Massachusetts was abolished.  Thus it is no longer being included in this table.
The county taking its place among the 68 large counties in this table is DeKalb, Georgia.
